# DedgeAuth -- Architecture & Technology

## Architecture Overview

- **DedgeAuth.Core**: Models (User, App, AppPermission, Tenant, LoginToken, RefreshToken, UserVisit), AuthConfiguration. No dependencies on Data or Api.
- **DedgeAuth.Data**: Entity Framework `AuthDbContext`, PostgreSQL via Npgsql. Depends only on Core.
- **DedgeAuth.Services**: AuthService, JwtTokenService, DatabaseSeeder. Depends on Core and Data.
- **DedgeAuth.Api**: ASP.NET Core API; registers DbContext, services, JWT auth, controllers (Auth, Users, Apps, Permissions, Tenants, Visits, Debug, UI). Serves static login UI from wwwroot. Port 8100.
- **DedgeAuth.Client**: Client library for consumer apps; AddDedgeAuth extension, AppRoleAuthorizationHandler, RequireAppPermission attribute, UI asset proxy (`/api/DedgeAuth/ui/{path}`). Depends only on Core.

## Technology

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|------------|
| Runtime | .NET 10 |
| API | ASP.NET Core 10, REST |
| Database | PostgreSQL, Npgsql.EntityFrameworkCore.PostgreSQL |
| Auth | JWT (Microsoft.IdentityModel.Tokens), BCrypt |
| Hosting | IIS virtual app (InProcess via AspNetCoreModuleV2), Kestrel port 8100 |
| IIS Deployment | `IIS-DeployApp.ps1` with `.deploy.json` profiles |
| API Docs | Scalar.AspNetCore (replaces Swashbuckle) |

## Conventions

- **Backend**: New auth features in Services; DB access via AuthDbContext. Use Core models; no EF entities across API boundary.
- **API**: PascalCase JSON; controllers return DTOs. Auth endpoints under `/api/auth`; apps, permissions, tenants, users under `/api/*`.
- **Database**: Table/column names snake_case; EF migrations in DedgeAuth.Data/Migrations.
- **Client library**: Consumer apps use `AddDedgeAuth(options)` and `[RequireAppPermission("Role")]`; JWT secret must match DedgeAuth server.

## Database Tables

| Table | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `users` | User accounts with BCrypt password hashes |
| `apps` | Registered consumer applications |
| `app_permissions` | Role-based permissions per app per user |
| `tenants` | Tenant branding (CSS, logo, icon, app routing) |
| `user_visits` | Visit tracking per user per app |
| `login_tokens` | Short-lived auth codes for code exchange |
| `refresh_tokens` | Long-lived refresh tokens |
